        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5368500?v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><p dir=\"auto\">In <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"2232922210\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/django-locallibrary-tutorial/issues/141\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/django-locallibrary-tutorial/issues/141/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/django-locallibrary-tutorial/issues/141\">mdn/django-locallibrary-tutorial#141</a> there is a question about whether the logout behaviour takes you to the admin logout view. It does not (if you have followed the tutorial). This makes it clear that you end up in the logout template page created earlier in this same topic/</p>",
